The Chains of the Ahl al-Hadith<br /><br />Part 4<br /><br />The chains and Ijāzah of Shaikh Ṣiddiq Ḥasan Khān [1307H] go through <br /><br />Shaikh Ḥussain bin Muḥsin Anṣārī al-Yamanī<br /><br />Shaikh Zain al-Aʿbidīn bin Muḥsin Anṣārī al-Yamanī<br /><br />Shaikh ʿAbdul Ḥaq Muḥaddith&gt;&gt;&gt; the Student of Imam Shawkānī<br /><br />Shaikh Yaḥya bin Muḥammad bin Aḥmad Ḥasan Ḥazimi, the Qāḍhi of Aʿden<br /><br />Muḥaddith Sayyid Nuʿmān Ālūsī, the Muftī of Baghdād<br /><br />Shaikh Shāh Muḥammad Yaʿqūb Muhajjar Makkī <br /><br />and also through Shaikh Shāh Waliullāḥ Dehlwī through his sons through Shaikh Sadr al-Din [1285H]<br /><br /><br />Shaikh Ṣiddiq Ḥasan Khān also had strong links and ties with the Scholars of Najd, from the likes of <br /><br />Shaikh Rāshid bin ʿAlī bin ʿAbdullāh bin Suleimān Najdī,<br /><br />Shaikh Ḥamd bin ʿAtiq<br /><br />the Hanbali Mufti of Makkah, Shaikh Muḥammad bin ʿAbdullāh bin Ḥumaid<br /><br />Shaikh ʿAbdullāh bin Rāshid Najdī<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=48">AbuKhuzaimahAnsari</a> — Fri Sep 30, 2016 10:21 pm</p><hr />
